Defendant Matthew A Cotton in court with attorney Mark P. Powers.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case called for sentencing hearing. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   
 

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT  
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with:  any co-actor or the victim or their employees
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

RESTITUTION: to be determined

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 6 months, 1st 3 months with huber for work/treatment, last 3 months STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours. Defendant to report by 03/07/2016 by 6 pm.   

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

Any bail to be applied to costs/surcharges and refund the balance to the poster
Attorney to submit any credit time within 2 weeks  Restitution hearing scheduled for April 25, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
